msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "3. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Kasiṇasutta "
msgstr "25. Meditation on Universals "

# NOTE: BB perpetuates the mistake that kasina means “disk” in the suttas. It does not, as should be obvious from this sutta. It means “universal”. The root means “universal, totality”. It is not a term for the physical object on which meditation is based, but for the “universal, non-dual, measureless” state of mind produced by meditation. As such it is virtually a synonym for samadhi, but used in a more specific sense.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.46, sc1
msgctxt "an10.25:1.1"
msgid "“Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, kasiṇāyatanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these ten universal dimensions of meditation. "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni dasa? "
msgstr "What ten? "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.3"
msgid "Pathavīkasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ; "
msgstr "Someone perceives the meditation on universal earth above, below, across, non-dual and limitless. "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.4"
msgid "āpokasiṇameko sañjānāti … pe … "
msgstr "They perceive the meditation on universal water … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.5"
msgid "tejokasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal fire … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.6"
msgid "vāyokasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal air … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.7"
msgid "nīlakasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal blue … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.8"
msgid "pītakasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal yellow … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.9"
msgid "lohitakasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal red … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.10"
msgid "odātakasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal white … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.11"
msgid "ākāsakasiṇameko sañjānāti … "
msgstr "the meditation on universal space … "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.12"
msgid "viññāṇakasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "They perceive the meditation on universal consciousness above, below, across, non-dual and limitless. "

msgctxt "an10.25:1.13"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa kasiṇāyatanānī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the ten universal dimensions of meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.25:1.14"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

